cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on hardware-software partitioning in embedded systems.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with the design and optimization of hardware and software components in a system.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of model checking to verify the correctness of the system design.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses bounded model checking and satisfiability modulo theories to solve the optimization problem.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of Open Multi-Processing (OpenMP) to support multi-core model checking.
